WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.009 --> 00:00:01.850
When an incident suggests a known issue,

1
00:00:02.009 --> 00:00:04.789
start by checking whether guidance already exists.

2
00:00:05.010 --> 00:00:06.449
In service operations workspace,

3
00:00:06.570 --> 00:00:09.630
knowledge search is available through the agent assist side panel.

4
00:00:12.850 --> 00:00:16.469
Use the filter menu to confirm that knowledge is included in the search scope.

5
00:00:17.709 --> 00:00:21.030
The search bar is pre-populated with the incident short description.

6
00:00:21.270 --> 00:00:24.950
You can adjust the search terms if needed to surface the most relevant articles.

7
00:00:25.719 --> 00:00:28.739
Your search results are displayed in cards in the side panel,

8
00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:31.639
and you can preview the articles within the sidebar itself,

9
00:00:31.719 --> 00:00:33.319
so you don't need to navigate elsewhere.

10
00:00:36.400 --> 00:00:39.200
You can open the article in full view in a separate tab

11
00:00:39.400 --> 00:00:41.520
to confirm the article content before sharing.

12
00:00:42.819 --> 00:00:45.090
If the article is suitable for the affected user,

13
00:00:45.540 --> 00:00:48.209
and it belongs to a knowledge base the user can access,

14
00:00:48.659 --> 00:00:50.759
you can send it to them by clicking attach.

15
00:00:51.020 --> 00:00:54.139
This allows you to send a link to the article with an additional comment.

16
00:00:59.520 --> 00:01:01.439
The link will open the article in the appropriate

17
00:01:01.439 --> 00:01:03.939
self-service portal view based on the user's permissions.